text: Buzat () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Buzatovsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 722 as of 2010. There are 9 streets. == Geography == It is located 47 km from Sterlibashevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Buzat, Sterlibashevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
